      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SUGAR PIE HONEY (7) resumes following a spell of five months but generally comes to hand very quickly with two wins and a placing from four first-up appearances. Won her first two starts of last campaign before finishing a head second to race rival GUNNA RELOAD in the G1 Breeders Challenge Final when last seen. Draws inside that rival and has beaten her before. GUNNA RELOAD (8) cops the outside barrier but is an accomplished mare who went to the paddock off a hat trick of wins, highlighted by that Breeders Challenge victory when last seen in October. Should be ready to go off two trials. PEACE OUT (6) last appeared when fifth at Menangle three-and-a-half months ago but had good form prior, winning a Breeders Crown heat at Melton and placing in the Vicbred Super Series final. Proven fresh and has been readied with three trials. CERISE RAINBOW (5) is going well with a string of wins or placings and draws better than in her narrow last-start defeat at Menangle.",
